# Database Sync Implementation Plan (Option C)

Based on your selection, we will implement **Option C: Dropbox/OneDrive Event Sync**. This serverless approach relies entirely on a shared sync folder.

## Core Mechanism (How it works)
1. **Sync Folder:** A folder mapped to Dropbox/OneDrive.
2. **Exporting:** When a user creates/edits a Song, SetList, or Preset, the app saves it locally to Isar, and also writes a tiny `event_[uuid].json` file to the Sync Folder. 
3. **Machine ID:** Each KeryxPro installation will generate a random `machineId` upon first launch. This ensures the app ignores its own exported JSON events when scanning the Sync folder.
4. **Mandatory Schema Change:** All synced entities (`Song`, `SavedSetlist`, `PresentationSettings`, `BibleVersion`) will receive a `syncId` (UUID) field to prevent ID collisions.

## Answering Your Questions / Required Approvals

> **1) Where can we give option to the user to select the sync folder?**

**Proposal:** I will add a new menu item in the Settings screen (e.g., "Database Sync" or "Storage & Sync"). 
This menu will contain a simple UI:
